> On 10/23/2016 at 2:13 AM, SpaceTiger said:
> 
> 
> You are still using an old version(1.4.0) of the [KerboKatzUtilities](http://kerbokatz.github.io/#KerboKatzUtilities). Try upgrading it to the newest(1.4.5) version.
> 

So, I think I figured this out.  The download for the PhysicalTimeRatioViewer contains the KerboKatzUtilities.dll file.  If I just copy and paste the whole thing from one GameData folder to the other, the PhysicalTimeRatioViewer overwrites the updated .dll file, and causes things to break.

If I then reinstall the 1.4.5 version of KerboKatzUtilities, it corrects the issue.  

Maybe don't bundle the Utilities file with the .dll?  Or perhaps the PhysicalTimeRatioViewer package contains the wrong .dll file?  Not sure, but I think that's where the issue stemmed from.

Thanks for your help, and for the great mods.  I certainly appreciate both.

Figured something along those lines happened. The KerboKatzUtilities bundled is the newest version at release time. Sometimes only the KerboKatzUtilities require an update for things to work.

They are bundled like that cause one can forget the KerboKatzUtilities and wonder why it doesn't work at all, its a drop and done kinda installation. Usually it's a good idea to download the latest version of the KerboKatzUtilities and install it as the last step.
